			    STPJS 18</div>
  <p class="cont">glory to Him, for the hour of His judgment is come.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">1</span> Repent ye, repent ye, and embrace the
  everlasting covenant,<span class="footRef">2</span> and flee to Zion,<span class="footRef">3</span> before the overflowing scourge<span class="footRef">4</span> overtake you, for there are
  those now living upon the earth whose eyes shall not be closed in death until they see all these
  things, which I have spoken, fulfilled. Remember these things; call upon the Lord while He is near,
  and seek Him while He may be found,<span class="footRef">5</span> is the exhortation of your unworthy servant.</p>
  <p class="right">(Signed) JOSEPH SMITH, JUN.&mdash;DHC 1:312–316.</p>
  <div class="topic">Important Correspondence With the Brethren in Zion</div>
  <p class="summary">The &ldquo;Olive Leaf&rdquo;<span class="footRef">6</span> is the name given by the Prophet to the wonderful revelation known as Sec. 88, in the <i>Doctrine</i>
  <i>and Covenants</i>. There are few, if any, revelations given to the Church&mdash;and to the world if the world will receive
  them&mdash;greater than this &ldquo;Olive Leaf, plucked from the Tree of Paradise.&rdquo;  In this letter to W. W. Phelps, one of the
  presiding brethren in Missouri, the Prophet raises a warning voice based upon the word of the Lord as revealed in the
  revelation and correspondence from Missouri.</p>
  <hr class="centerQuarter" />
  <p class="salutation"><div class="salutation">Brother William W. Phelps:</div><div class="placeDate">Kirtland, January 14, 1833.</div></p>
  <p class="std">I send you the &ldquo;olive leaf&rdquo;<span class="footRef">7</span> which we have plucked from the Tree of Paradise,<span class="footRef">8</span> the Lord&rsquo;s
  message of peace to us; for though our brethren in Zion indulge in feelings towards us, which are
  not according to the requirements of the new covenant,<span class="footRef">9</span> yet, we have the satisfaction of knowing that
  the Lord approves of us,<span class="footRef">10</span> and has accepted us, and established His name in Kirtland<span class="footRef">11</span> for the
  salvation of the nations;<span class="footRef">12</span> for the Lord will have a place whence His word will go forth,<span class="footRef">13</span> in these
  last days, in purity; for if Zion will not purify herself,<span class="footRef">14</span> so as to be approved of in all things,<span class="footRef">15</span> in His
  sight, He will seek another people;<span class="footRef">16</span> for His work will go on until Israel is gathered,<span class="footRef">17</span> and they who
  will not hear His voice,<span class="footRef">18</span> must expect to feel His wrath.<span class="footRef">19</span> Let me say unto you, seek to purify
  yourselves,<span class="footRef">20</span> and also the inhabitants of Zion,<span class="footRef">21</span> lest the Lord&rsquo;s anger be kindled to fierceness.<span class="footRef">22</span></p>
  <div class="topic">A Warning to Zion</div>
  <p class="std">Repent, repent, is the voice of God to Zion;<span class="footRef">23</span> and strange as it may appear, yet it is true,
